summary.overview:
- Andrew and Joe prepared for Levy meeting to review project progress and discussed action items from the previous meeting on the 9th.  
- Successful migration from N8N to a custom web application enhances storage and human-in-the-loop editing before integration with Monday.com.  
- Manual categorization feature added to the dashboard, improving action item classification without causing integration issues.  
- Joe identified three main technical challenges, including column mapping difficulties with Monday.com.  
- Implementation of a GitHub-first strategy prevents destructive coding practices and ensures version control with rollback capabilities.  
- Three key deliverables for the Levy meeting include N8N flow redesign, Monday.com integration, and Discord connectivity, with a focus on showcasing progress.  
- Custom web application allows manual control for meeting transcription, offering an admin dashboard for better meeting management.  
- Levy will be able to modify prompts through the admin interface, eliminating the need for complex N8N workflows.  
- Demo preparation includes showcasing Fireflies integration and processing meetings via a command prompt, enhancing transparency.  
- Meeting with Levy rescheduled to 3 PM, and the team confirmed confidence in project direction despite existing technical challenges.

summary.shorthand_bullet:
📋 **Meeting Preparation and Task Review** (16:32 - 22:38)
Andrew and Joe preparing for upcoming meeting with Levy to review project progress
Reviewing action items from previous Monday meeting (9th) using ChatGPT analysis
Multiple tasks completed including export/import of workflows from Joe's personal instance
Fireflies fetch frequency increased to 3 hours with deduplication - now completely overhauled
Multi-agent cross-specific boards task still pending and requires Monday.com integration
🔧 **Technical Architecture Migration** (20:46 - 23:00)
Joe migrated entire system from N8N to custom web application for better functionality
Migration necessary to achieve storage capabilities and human-in-the-loop editing before pushing to Monday.com
LLM needs transcript context connected to Monday.com to properly categorize action items into correct projects
Manual categorization feature added to dashboard allowing users to move items between projects
Current approach prevents mayhem and reduces need for corrections compared to direct integration
🐛 **Current Technical Challenges** (23:24 - 25:46)
Joe running tests to solve three main problems with the system
Successfully connected to Monday.com but column mapping proving challenging
Dashboard broke when switching from dummy data to live Monday.com board integration
Processing and action item extraction components are complete and working
Post-processing functionality to meet company criteria also implemented successfully
📚 **Development Strategy and Version Control** (25:46 - 27:19)
Joe learned importance of incorporating GitHub from the beginning of development
Previous strategy of local development then GitHub export proved destructive
AI agents would delete working code while attempting to solve current problems
New GitHub-first strategy ensures nothing goes to production without passing tests
Version control allows rollback to previously working state when AI causes issues
🎯 **Meeting Strategy and Deliverables** (28:08 - 30:30)
Three main deliverables identified for Levy meeting: N8N flow redesign, Monday.com integration, and Discord piece
N8N flow completed with storage and human-in-the-loop editing capabilities
Monday.com integration dependent on first deliverable and requires mapping work
GitHub integration added for version control, with potential for API querying and plugin integration
Focus on demonstrating progress even if not fully complete
🌐 **Web Application Features and Control** (33:07 - 36:22)
Custom web application provides manual control Levy requested for meeting transcription
Admin dashboard allows muting specific meetings to prevent Monday.com integration
System maintains accountability by logging which meetings were stopped and by whom
Levy can modify prompts directly through admin interface rather than complex N8N workflows
Web app enables all desired functionality that N8N couldn't provide with proper storage
💻 **Demo Preparation and Technical Showcase** (37:26 - 40:06)
Joe will demonstrate system using command prompt showing Fireflies integration
Demo will show downloading meetings, processing them, and generating JSON action items
Interface uses ready-made templates from AI tool discussed previously
Levy's programming background will help him understand the technical implementation
Code resides in GitHub allowing Levy to review at any time rather than copy-paste sharing
📅 **Meeting Scheduling and Next Steps** (40:28 - 42:01)
Meeting with Levy rescheduled from 11 AM to 12 PM, then finally to 3 PM
Andrew will send calendar invite to Levy for ops meeting review
Joe requested additional time to ensure proper preparation and avoid over-promising
Future integration plans include Discord connectivity and master knowledge base for Twitter
Team confident in direction and progress despite technical challenges

summary.short_summary: Andrew and Joe prepared for the Levy meeting to assess project progress and address action items from the previous meeting on the 9th. They highlighted the successful migration from N8N to a custom web application, which improves storage and supports human-in-the-loop editing before integration with Monday.com. A new manual categorization feature on the dashboard enhances action item classification without integration issues. Joe pointed out three technical challenges, particularly column mapping with Monday.com. The team is implementing a GitHub-first strategy to ensure version control and prevent destructive coding practices. Three main deliverables for the Levy meeting include the redesign of the N8N flow, integration with Monday.com, and Discord connectivity. The custom web application provides manual control for meeting transcription, and Levy will be able to modify prompts through an admin interface, simplifying workflows. The meeting was rescheduled to 3 PM, and the team expressed confidence in the project despite existing challenges.
